### Lexical Editor Theme for Lists

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-list/README.md

This example illustrates how to define theme classes for list elements within a Lexical editor's configuration. It covers styling for unordered lists (ul), ordered lists (ol), list items (listitem), and nested list structures.

```typescript
const editorConfig = {
    // ... other config
    theme: {
        list: {
            ul: 'my-ul-class',
            ulDepth: ['my-ul-level-one', 'my-ul-level-two'],
            ol: 'my-ol-class',
            olDepth: ['my-ol-level-one', 'my-ol-level-two'],
            listitem: 'my-listitem-class',
            listitemChecked: 'my-listitem-checked-class',
            listitemUnchecked: 'my-listitem-unchecked-class',
            nested: {
                list: 'my-nested-list-class',
                listitem: 'my-nested-listitem-class'
            }
        }
    }
};

```

