### Internal Node Pointer Structure (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/key-management.md

Provides a look at the internal structure of a Lexical node, emphasizing how keys are used for internal pointers like `__prev`, `__next`, and `__parent`. This structure is crucial for maintaining the node hierarchy and should not be directly modified.

```typescript
// Internal node structure (not for direct usage)
{
  __prev: null | NodeKey,
  __next: null | NodeKey,
  __parent: null | NodeKey,
  // __first, __last and __size are only for ElementNode to track its children
  __first: null | NodeKey,
  __last: null | NodeKey,
  __size: number
}
```

