### Lexical ElementNode - Node Behavior

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/nodes.mdx

Provides an overview of `ElementNode` in Lexical, highlighting its role as a parent for other nodes and its customizable behavior. Key methods like `isInline`, `canBeEmpty`, and `canInsertTextBefore` can be overridden.

```javascript
import { ElementNode } from 'lexical';

class CustomElementNode extends ElementNode {
  static getType() {
    return 'custom-element';
  }

  static clone(node) {
    return new CustomElementNode(node.getMode(), node.getKey());
  }

  // Override methods like isInline, canBeEmpty, etc.
  isInline() {
    return false; // Example: Making it a block node
  }
}
```

