### ChildCaret Construction and Usage (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/traversals.md

Illustrates the construction of a ChildCaret and its methods for accessing and manipulating child nodes within an ElementNode. It explains the 'next' direction for the first child and 'previous' for the last child.

```typescript
import { $getChildCaret, CaretDirection, ElementNode } from 'lexical';

// Example usage for 'next' direction (first child)
const elementNode: ElementNode = ...; // Assume elementNode is an ElementNode
const firstChildCaret = $getChildCaret(elementNode, 'next');
const firstChildNode = firstChildCaret.getNodeAtCaret(); // Gets the first child
// firstChildCaret.insert(newNode); // Inserts newNode as the first child

// Example usage for 'previous' direction (last child)
const lastChildCaret = $getChildCaret(elementNode, 'previous');
const lastChildNode = lastChildCaret.getNodeAtCaret(); // Gets the last child
// lastChildCaret.insert(newNode); // Appends newNode as the last child
```

